It's so funny that until like 100 years ago pharmaceutical drugs basically didn't exist so doctors were just stuck endlessly debating hot baths versus cold baths or from what region of France did the most healthful wine come

Like in the 17th century medicine professors were having flamewars writing treatises against each other's regional wines with one side accusing champagne of causing gout and the other saying champagne was the key to longevity and the other guys' wine was 100% poison. Keyed world.

Listening to a Dr. Gerald Pollack podcast is so funny because he straight up just responds with "I don't really know" or "probably, I'm not sure" to every single question. Like the host asked him about EZ water and redox and he just said he doesn't really know what redox even is.
